Interface IGameObject

All Known Subinterfaces:
IItem
All Known Implementing Classes:
Arrow, Coin, FreezeItem, GameObject, Goal, Character, Item, RageItem, Sheep, Start, Tile, Wolf
public interface IGameObject
Interface representing any game object. A game object can be rendered, updated, and has a position in the game world.

  • Method Details

    • isVisible

      boolean isVisible()
      Checks if the game object is visible.
      Returns:
      true if the object is visible, false otherwise.

    • tick

      void tick(boolean doesTimeFlow)
      Updates the game object, by specified behavior.
      Parameters:
      doesTimeFlow - Whether time is currently flowing (true if the scene is rendering, and only during that the time limit clock flows).

    • resetLevel

      void resetLevel()
      Resets the game object to its initial state. Used when loading / resting the level. It will clear all the static variables if the class uses them. (Like the total number of coins collected, etc.)

    • getRenderPriority

      int getRenderPriority()
      Returns the render priority of the game object. The lower the number, the more in the background it is rendered. The higher the number, the more in the foreground it is rendered.
      Returns:
      The render priority of the game object.

    • getPosition

      double[] getPosition()
      Returns the tile-converted position of the game object in the game world.
      Returns:
      The position of the game object as an array of doubles.

    • setPosition

      void setPosition(double[] position)
      Sets the tile-converted position of the game object in the game world.
      Parameters:
      position - The new position of the game object as an array of doubles.

    • getTexture

      javafx.scene.image.Image getTexture()
      Returns the texture of the game object.
      Returns:
      The texture of the game object as an Image.

    • getTextureSize

      int[] getTextureSize()
      Returns the size of the texture of the game object in pixels.
      Returns:
      The size of the texture as an array of integers.
